    <h2>One of our busiest service areas — and the most diverse</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Los Angeles County is where we do most of our work. The county covers 10 million people across communities as different as the beachfront estates in Malibu and the multi-unit apartment stock in Koreatown. A Beverly Hills home with a built-in Sub-Zero and a Culver City apartment with a stacked Bosch washer-dryer are both in the same county — and both get the same same-day service from the same licensed, insured technicians.</p>
      <p>The appliance landscape in LA County is probably the most varied in the country. Older craftsman homes in Pasadena and Burbank running Whirlpool and GE appliances that have been in service for 15 years. New construction luxury condos in WeHo with Samsung and LG packages. Estates in Pacific Palisades and Brentwood with full Sub-Zero, Wolf, and Thermador kitchens. We see all of it.</p>
      <p>The county also has two distinct climate profiles that affect appliances differently. Coastal cities — Santa Monica, Malibu, Marina del Rey, Manhattan Beach — have salt air that accelerates coil corrosion and gasket wear. We recommend maintenance every 4–6 months for refrigerators in these areas, not the standard 12. Inland communities in the San Fernando Valley deal with dry, dusty conditions that clog condenser coils faster. Same day appliance repair across Los Angeles County means knowing these differences and factoring them in.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

