        <p class="sl">LA County Appliance Context</p>
        <h2>Why LA County appliances need county-specific knowledge</h2>
        <p>No other county in California has the combination of housing diversity, appliance brand diversity, and climate variation that LA County does. Our technicians cover Beverly Hills estate kitchens with $30,000 Sub-Zero and Wolf setups in the morning and apartment buildings in Koreatown with Whirlpool appliances that have been running since 2005 in the afternoon.</p>
        <p>The two GMB locations serving LA County — West Hollywood (323) 870-4790 for the Westside and close-in communities, Los Angeles (424) 325-0520 for the broader county — give us faster dispatch times across the full geographic spread. From Malibu to Long Beach is a significant drive. Having technicians positioned across the county means same day actually means same day.</p>
        <p>Same day appliance repair in Los Angeles County is our main business. We've built it around what the county actually needs: fast response, honest diagnosis, and technicians who know the difference between a Beverly Hills luxury kitchen and a Burbank craftsman rental.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="context-facts">
        <div class="cfact"><h4>🏠 Most diverse housing stock in the US</h4><p>1920s craftsman in Pasadena, 1970s concrete in Koreatown, 2020s luxury high-rise in WeHo — we service all of it.</p></div>
